:INFO
The Novel I Found Twenty Years Late and Cannot Forgive Myself For
I was 34 when I first read Zora Neale Hurston and the feeling I had when I \
finished Their Eyes Were Watching God was grief about the years I had not been \
reading it. The novel is about Janie Crawford, a Black woman in early \
twentieth-century Florida who lives three marriages and refuses to let any of \
them define her. Hurston's prose is unlike anything else in American literature: \
specific, lyrical, and written in the dialect of the people it is about with \
complete respect for that language.

:NOW
Thinking about why I waited so long to read this

:QUOTE [subtitle:Zora Neale Hurston, quotetype:PLAIN]
Ships at a distance have every man's wish on board.

:JOURNEY
Reading Their Eyes Were Watching God
Section
Impact
- Nanny chapters | 4 | World established | Sets up the world Janie is moving through
- Joe Starks years | 5 | Silencing marriage | Most precise account of that particular harm
- Tea Cake sections | 5 | Complicated love | Hurston refuses to simplify what is there
- The ending | 5 | Assertion of self | Among the most powerful endings in American fiction

